<span id="freeTextContainer14220995370260238948">I have read 8 of Carson McCullers books, and like the rest of the world I agree that this is her best work. It sets a tone that I found prevailing in almost all of her books, a sad and melancholy outlook on life, and being a young and impressionable eccentric in 1940&apos;s small town Georgia, I can understand that. This is her masterpiece. It was made into a 1968 movie starring Alan Arkin and it is firmly placed in the list of best American novels.<br/>4.5 stars<br/><br/>Side note: Sunday, Feb. 19, 2017, will mark</span>
  <span id="freeText14220995370260238948" style="display:none">I have read 8 of Carson McCullers books, and like the rest of the world I agree that this is her best work. It sets a tone that I found prevailing in almost all of her books, a sad and melancholy outlook on life, and being a young and impressionable eccentric in 1940's small town Georgia, I can understand that. This is her masterpiece. It was made into a 1968 movie starring Alan Arkin and it is firmly placed in the list of best American novels.<br />4.5 stars<br /><br />Side note: Sunday, Feb. 19, 2017, will mark the 100th Birthday of Carson McCullers.</span>
